Noun
a compound that is a salt or ester of a xanthic acid and that is usually colorless and soluble in the case of the alkali metal salts but yellow and insoluble in the case of the copper salts <sodium xanthate> <potassium butyl xanthate C4H9OCSSK> -- compare VISCOSE
Verb
to convert (as alkali cellulose) into a xanthate by reaction with carbon disulfide -- compare SULFIDE